{"ts":"2026-06-26T18:57:09.735Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Calculator Implementation**\n\nI'm evaluating whether to build a custom calculation formula within the page or leverage our existing utility with `shared-validation.ts`. My initial thought leans toward enhancing the current setup, but I need to ensure it can handle all the specific inputs needed for the prompt.\n\n\n**Defining Input Parameters**\n\nI've nailed down the precise input parameters. The prompt demands industry, company size, function, annual cost baseline, process volume, optional average handling time, automation target percentage, current manual effort level, expected productivity improvement range, and implementation horizon. Now I need to design the UI for these fields, remembering safe validation for numbers and non-negative currency/volume inputs.\n\n\n**Designing Calculator Mathematics**\n\nI'm now outlining the mathematical structure of the calculator. I've broken down all the inputs that are necessary and the need for rigorous validation of each one. The selected parameters will feed into a formula. I'm focusing on non-negative number validation to ensure calculations are sound. I have also decided on some default values to improve usability.\n\n\n**Modeling Savings Formulas**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the savings calculation formulas. I have determined the inputs I need for a useful calculation. I'm focusing on how to combine these inputs, especially relating to addressable cost, which stems from the annual cost baseline and automation target percentage. I am evaluating different approaches to account for the impact of `manualEffort` and productivity improvements. I am considering this for the frontend only, so this is just the model.\n\n\n**Refining Savings Calculation Logic**\n\nI'm now refining the savings logic based on the specific inputs. I'm focusing on incorporating `avgHandlingTime` and `processVolume` to calculate reclaimed hours and a blended hourly cost. I am thinking through how to model implementation investment, especially regarding `companySize` and `annualCostBaseline` to determine a reasonable deployment investment. I want to limit `estimatedAnnualSavings` to 90% of `annualCostBaseline`.\n\n\n**Calculating ROI Projections**\n\nI'm now determining the core calculations for net savings, ROI, and payback horizon. I have equations ready, which now factor in the implementation investment. I'll need to clearly show this is a *modeled* result, not a guarantee. I'm also planning to incorporate a milestone roadmap based on the implementation horizon selection, for added context. I'll make sure to add the necessary disclaimers about the illustrative and non-guaranteed nature of the projections.\n\n\n**Designing Premium UI**\n\nI'm now focusing on UI design. I'm prioritizing a dual-pane layout: Input controls on the left and a dynamic side preview on the right. I'm organizing the inputs into collapsible sections: Enterprise Profile & Friction Baseline, and Financials & Operational Friction. I'm exploring segmented controls for \"Company Size\" and dropdowns for \"Industry\" and \"Functional Domain\", with inputs like \"Annual Cost Baseline\" and \"Process Volume\" featuring validation. I'm also planning for optional inputs, like \"Average Handling Time\", to maintain smooth calculation flow.\n\n\n**Visualizing Sovereign Goals**\n\nI'm now integrating the user's sovereign automation goals into the UI. I have added controls for automation target percentage (a range slider with a live indicator), current manual effort level (segmented buttons), expected productivity improvement range (another range slider), and the implementation horizon (segmented buttons). On the right side, I am designing a live, interactive dashboard previewing the estimated projections, complete with a \"RECALCULATING LIVE...\" status. I'm focusing on key performance indicators with a bento-grid layout, which will include reclaimed capital (net savings), estimated Year 1 ROI, payback milestone, and reclaimed operational time (if applicable), all within a custom workflow map visualization.\n\n\n**Adding Deployment Roadmaps**\n\nI'm now integrating a deployment roadmap based on the implementation horizon. I've defined milestones such as \"Enclave Provisioning,\" \"Ingest & Training,\" and \"Production Launch,\" each with clear timelines. I'm also including an \"Simulate Enterprise Run\" button to show a high-end AI deployment specification sheet to drive value. Finally, I'm integrating several design elements, including agent workflow maps.\n\n\n"}}
