{"ts":"2026-06-26T18:58:51.211Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Evaluating Tool Functionality**\n\nI'm thrilled with the tools! Their cleanliness, robustness, and visual appeal are inspiring. My focus has shifted to crafting a top-tier executive ROI calculator. I'm planning to leverage `ToolPageShell` for the global statuses, VPC telemetry, data perimeter, etc. and a beautiful custom stateful page within `app/build/roi/page`.\n\n\n**Refining Calculator Implementation**\n\nI'm focused on the ROI calculator's `/app/build/roi/page.tsx` state structure. I've confirmed `motion/react` is installed, which is great. Now, I'm thinking about the UI: a left-side input panel and a real-time preview on the right. Mobile responsiveness is also a priority; they should stack neatly. I'm planning the state with `ROICalculatorState`, handling string inputs to maintain input editing.\n\n\n**Defining Validation Logic**\n\nI'm now detailing validation for the ROI calculator's inputs, specifically for numbers and non-negative values. I've defined `ValidationErrorState` to manage potential input errors. I'll implement validation rules for `annualCostBaseline`, `processVolume`, and the optional `avgHandlingTime`, with real-time error feedback using red warning text.\n\n\n**Implementing Live Calculation**\n\nI'm now implementing the live calculation. With no validation errors, I'll securely parse input values like `costBaseline`, `volume`, and `handlingTime`. Then, I'll determine expected annual savings, including `automationTargetPercent`, `improvementPercent`, and an `effortMultiplier` based on manual effort. Finally, I will cap `estimatedSavings` at 95% of the total baseline. If there are validation errors, I will display \"Fix validation errors to update model projection.\"\n\n\n**Calculating Investment Details**\n\nNow I'm modeling the recommended investment cost for single-tenant VPC nodes, using base costs scaled by company size. I'll add a variable component tied to annual cost baseline and volume, calculating a total investment. I'll define reclaimed capital after the first year as net savings minus total investment. Then, I will compute the ROI percentage and payback horizon. Finally, I will calculate reclaimed hours per year.\n\n\n**Designing Dashboard Preview**\n\nI'm now focused on the executive dashboard preview, envisioning an interactive Bento Grid with key metrics. I will show Net Savings with a sliding scale, ROI with an arrow up, Payback Period in months, and Reclaimed Hours. If handling time is provided, it will show \"X,XXX hours/yr\", otherwise, a placeholder. I will also incorporate an SVG/CSS agent workflow roadmap, with milestones based on implementation horizon.\n\n\n**Envisioning Interactive UI**\n\nI'm now focusing on UI micro-interactions. I'm keen on making the ROI calculator feel premium and responsive. I'm planning to use sliders with customized track colors and real-time numeric displays to make the range inputs feel polished. I also plan to add segmented controls for a refined user experience, which should give it that extra level of polish.\n\n\n**Crafting Premium Report**\n\nI'm now diving into the \"Simulation Detail Report\" overlay. I want it to be a real \"Wow!\" moment. I'm focusing on those tailored narrative summaries that will be specific to the user's input, like \"SOVEREIGN ENCLAVE ARCHITECTURE BLUEPRINT FOR BANKING\" and related custom recommendations based on their choices. The goal is to make it feel premium, strategic, and completely personalized. I want to include a strong call to action, too.\n\n\n**Reviewing File Dependencies**\n\nI'm now auditing the imports within `/app/build/roi/page.tsx` to understand the existing dependencies before considering updates. I see we have access to `ToolPageShell`, `ToolInputGroup`, `ToolCTA`, and other layout elements, alongside validation and calculation helpers. I am deciding how best to build my custom